1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:00,110 --> 00:00:03,330
Try them on one more time and you'll see I'm right.

3
00:00:03,470 --> 00:00:06,710
I could try them on a thousand times and every time I'd find they're hideous.

4
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:09,410
They're not hideous, they're appropriate.

5
00:00:10,070 --> 00:00:10,550
Appropriate.

6
00:00:10,550 --> 00:00:14,550
Iva, you look so nice today, you look so, you know, appropriate.

7
00:00:14,550 --> 00:00:15,950
A dress should cover you up.

8
00:00:16,550 --> 00:00:19,930
But when I went to dance class, me and my partner had a great dress.

9
00:00:19,930 --> 00:00:22,070
I only found out she had a hump at the wine reception.

10
00:00:22,470 --> 00:00:24,250
In this dress nobody will notice me.

11
00:00:24,730 --> 00:00:26,090
Well then they'll assign you someone.

12
00:00:26,290 --> 00:00:30,010
Look, they assigned me Magdička too and our waltz was written about in the paper.

13
00:00:30,170 --> 00:00:31,250
In the crime section?

14
00:00:31,550 --> 00:00:33,390
No, in the tabloids.

15
00:00:34,050 --> 00:00:37,650
And is that why Strýra Harapes calls you zero?

16
00:00:38,350 --> 00:00:39,750
No, that's unrelated.

17
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:44,250
The saleswoman said she bought the same ones for her daughter.

18
00:00:48,050 --> 00:00:50,950
Dance class isn't some fashion show.

19
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:02,450
Oh boy, now those are some dress.

20
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:05,770
Iva, Saša is here and she has a dress.

21
00:01:06,050 --> 00:01:06,550
I'm gonna kill myself.

22
00:01:13,950 --> 00:01:15,150
I'll stay alive after all.

23
00:01:16,290 --> 00:01:17,070
Sorry, Saša.

24
00:01:46,650 --> 00:01:48,070
Did you see the dress Kropáčková has?

25
00:01:48,450 --> 00:01:50,570
The way she was showing off in it in front of the gym.

26
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:53,320
I couldn't get to her through the crowd of boys.

27
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:59,450
If Tokarská hadn't barged in and given her a note for parading around school in a slip, Beneš's eyes would have popped out.

28
00:02:01,350 --> 00:02:04,350
But if I had those other dress, I would've trumped her.

29
00:02:04,580 --> 00:02:06,280
They're at least hidden away for a special occasion.

30
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,360
What other dress?

31
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,520
They're called exactly what you need to impress boys.

32
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,420
Iva, tennis?

33
00:02:13,850 --> 00:02:15,220
First instinct.

34
00:02:15,650 --> 00:02:17,250
In those, boys would be lining up for me.

35
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:21,450
I'd be happy if at least Voráček came for me.

36
00:02:22,050 --> 00:02:23,000
That could work.

37
00:02:23,350 --> 00:02:27,050
After a few shots, he'll crawl up a street lamp.

38
00:02:27,550 --> 00:02:28,250
Sorry, Saša.

39
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:31,200
Hi.

40
00:02:33,350 --> 00:02:34,450
Like someone died.

41
00:02:36,390 --> 00:02:37,150
Drop dead, Lexa.

42
00:02:44,250 --> 00:02:45,730
Dance class was the bane of my existence.

43
00:02:45,850 --> 00:02:47,610
Yeah, dance class is evil.

44
00:02:47,610 --> 00:02:48,970
It takes away a person's natural ways.

45
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:52,950
You ran away from it, so luckily you kept your natural ways.

46
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:55,480
At least I didn't have to dance with a camel.

47
00:02:55,650 --> 00:02:57,450
Hey, don't talk about Magdička like that.

48
00:02:58,050 --> 00:02:59,860
That famous hunchback dancer?

49
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:02,350
I read about her once in the tabloids.

50
00:03:02,850 --> 00:03:03,380
See?

51
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,750
Apparently she had a hopeless dancer.

52
00:03:07,450 --> 00:03:08,540
Well that wasn't me.

53
00:03:08,850 --> 00:03:09,700
Yes it was.

54
00:03:10,150 --> 00:03:11,850
That's why Harapes calls him zero.

55
00:03:11,950 --> 00:03:12,350
But that was for something else.

56
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,540
Hey bro, don't you wanna go grab a beer?

57
00:03:15,720 --> 00:03:16,960
Nah, I find this interesting.

58
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:20,140
Tomáš, what kind of dress will Ivuška have?

59
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:21,960
Oh don't you start with that too.

60
00:03:22,350 --> 00:03:25,190
If he didn't go with her, she'd show up broke and practically naked.

61
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:27,570
I hope you didn't discuss the choice of dress with her.

62
00:03:28,150 --> 00:03:28,590
I didn't.

63
00:03:28,810 --> 00:03:29,950
You're a wise man.

64
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:33,950
My father tried to ban my dress, but he didn't succeed.

65
00:03:33,950 --> 00:03:35,170
I smuggled it in from East Germany.

66
00:03:35,390 --> 00:03:36,830
In a toothpaste tube.

67
00:03:37,370 --> 00:03:40,430
At dance class you're supposed to learn to dance, not show off.

68
00:03:40,570 --> 00:03:42,790
The most important dance in the world is pogo anyway.

69
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:44,990
And only master booze can teach you that.

70
00:03:45,310 --> 00:03:46,530
She's still a child, come on.

71
00:03:47,050 --> 00:03:49,650
Wait until you walk her through the hall at the extended evening.

72
00:03:49,650 --> 00:03:50,930
You'll see she's already a woman.

73
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:55,740
If she wore the dress I banned, everyone in the hall would see that too.

74
00:03:55,740 --> 00:03:58,150
Wait, what do you mean banned?

75
00:03:58,150 --> 00:03:59,930
Wait, what do you mean walk through the hall?

76
00:03:59,930 --> 00:04:01,550
Wait, what do you mean in a toothpaste tube?

77
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:06,250
At the parents-with-kids dance, even my father understood.

78
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:09,470
I escaped from him and from the tenth lesson danced the Letkiss at the Alhambra.

79
00:04:09,790 --> 00:04:11,750
Until the secret police confiscated our shoes.

80
00:04:14,450 --> 00:04:15,850
Wait, mambo, so you used to be a normal person?

81
00:04:19,350 --> 00:04:21,470
Listen to your brother and go get a beer.

82
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:23,170
What is it with all of you and beer?

83
00:04:23,450 --> 00:04:25,150
Do I look like someone who's thirsty?

84
00:04:26,450 --> 00:04:27,950
I am, but I can control it.

85
00:04:29,950 --> 00:04:33,350
Tomáš, didn't you dance with your mother at the extended evening?

86
00:04:33,370 --> 00:04:36,430
Well yeah, but I thought she was happy about it.

87
00:04:37,330 --> 00:04:38,590
Like, when she was wasted.

88
00:04:46,050 --> 00:04:47,650
That took a while.

89
00:04:49,150 --> 00:04:50,150
It had to be done.

90
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:52,240
Otherwise we wouldn't have gotten him out of here.

91
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:53,880
No, I mean the dancing.

92
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:54,820
Tomáš.

93
00:04:55,450 --> 00:04:56,950
Now it's going to be lovely.

94
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:58,080
Lovely?

95
00:04:59,650 --> 00:05:03,950
Maybe I should tell you why Harapes calls me zero.

96
00:05:07,850 --> 00:05:09,260
They straight up threw me out of the store.

97
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:12,550
I'd love to know what those two are cooking up in there.

98
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:14,450
Here's your lunch.

99
00:05:15,950 --> 00:05:16,950
Saša's not coming?

100
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:19,450
She's been throwing up since morning because of the dance class.

101
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:22,450
Fine, so that would've been wasted money anyway.

102
00:05:23,650 --> 00:05:26,050
That dance class, good thing I don't have to go.

103
00:05:26,550 --> 00:05:27,750
I put my foot down too.

104
00:05:28,050 --> 00:05:30,650
I don't have a suit, so no big deal.

105
00:05:30,850 --> 00:05:31,750
Cool dude.

106
00:05:32,050 --> 00:05:33,350
They couldn't force me either.

107
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:36,150
I ran away from home for three months and hid at the junkyard.

108
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,320
Hardcore.

109
00:05:38,550 --> 00:05:40,650
So I'm basically like you guys?

110
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:43,550
Lexa, a dude's gotta know how to stand up to the system.

111
00:05:45,450 --> 00:05:47,450
Lexa, go get changed.

112
00:05:49,750 --> 00:05:50,550
But mom, you said it's enough that Saša goes and then she'll teach me everything.

113
00:05:50,850 --> 00:05:57,950
Yeah, but that was before I found out there's a girl there who likes you.

114
00:05:58,350 --> 00:05:58,850
Really?

115
00:05:59,720 --> 00:06:00,120
Who?

116
00:06:01,850 --> 00:06:02,950
Young Krutová.

117
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,420
Titanic?

118
00:06:05,450 --> 00:06:07,250
She weighs 130 kilos now?

119
00:06:08,050 --> 00:06:12,380
Her mom is paying me fifty for every dance, so make sure she doesn't sit down for a single moment, got it?

120
00:06:12,750 --> 00:06:14,850
Mom, you can't sell me like this.

121
00:06:15,150 --> 00:06:17,050
Anything over 500 you can keep.

122
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:19,150
This is blackmail.

123
00:06:19,650 --> 00:06:21,650
No, this is blackmail.

124
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:28,250
Lexa, you're going to dance right now, or I'll tell Iva what you do every night in the bathroom with her photo.

125
00:06:28,650 --> 00:06:30,410
Oh, and you're supposed to wear white gloves.

126
00:06:30,850 --> 00:06:33,150
Here, doctor Slívat left these behind.

127
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:38,150
Mr. Ozzák, say something.

128
00:06:38,950 --> 00:06:40,090
Hey, Simona.

129
00:06:40,550 --> 00:06:42,030
Don't you feel like another beer?

130
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:42,770
I do.

131
00:06:42,770 --> 00:06:43,450
Well then.

132
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:47,750
But what about the rebellion against the system?

133
00:06:51,650 --> 00:06:55,350
If you climb into the dumpster around the corner, you'll be safe till morning.

134
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:03,550
Tomáš, as a singer, you must have moved somehow while singing.

135
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:06,550
I got through my whole career with the laundress.

136
00:07:06,850 --> 00:07:07,450
Excuse me?

137
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,360
Rinsing.

138
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:16,520
Hanging.

139
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:21,300
Winding the cord.

140
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,350
That can't possibly be everything.

141
00:07:24,470 --> 00:07:25,310
Well, there's also the ironing board.

142
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:26,650
But I forgot that one.

143
00:07:26,650 --> 00:07:30,050
Surely you must know at least one standard dance.

144
00:07:30,650 --> 00:07:35,370
Well, I don't know if it's standard, but I once rehearsed something with the group Berušky.

145
00:07:35,370 --> 00:07:36,670
Well, excellent.

146
00:07:37,210 --> 00:07:39,490
The parents' dance can be managed with one dance.

147
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:39,830
Show me.

148
00:07:39,930 --> 00:07:41,790
No, no, it's a solo dance.

149
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:44,990
Go ahead.

150
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:05,950
No, no, no, 

151
00:08:46,050 --> 00:08:47,140
More like some mushrooms.

152
00:08:47,550 --> 00:08:48,760
But really weird ones.

153
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,800
It's like a train station in here.

154
00:08:52,040 --> 00:08:52,880
What do you want?

155
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:54,900
Mom, I'm scared to go there.

156
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,140
Go on, it's just around the corner.

157
00:08:56,140 --> 00:08:58,940
No boy is going to come for me for sure.

158
00:08:59,550 --> 00:09:01,920
Dance class will change a lot of things in your life.

159
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:04,750
All the boys ignored me at dance class too.

160
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:05,480
Well I didn't.

161
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,850
But everything changes at dance class.

162
00:09:09,170 --> 00:09:09,770
Really?

163
00:09:10,850 --> 00:09:12,870
That's great then.

164
00:09:13,150 --> 00:09:14,250
Thanks, mom.

165
00:09:18,050 --> 00:09:21,270
It's nice having a daughter who falls for every piece of nonsense, isn't it?

166
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:37,250
Apart from that crash at the beginning, it went okay.

167
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:41,440
You mean when all the boys rushed to Kropáčková and their legs slipped?

168
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:45,360
Voráček had these chains, so he got to Kropáčková first.

169
00:09:45,420 --> 00:09:50,160
Yeah, but then Beneš took them, sprayed them in his face, and since then no one could peel him off Kropáčková.

170
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:52,880
Even so, her dress was absolutely hideous.

171
00:09:53,350 --> 00:09:56,000
What's the name of that dress anyway, first instinct?

172
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:56,680
Pavlov's reflex.

173
00:09:58,950 --> 00:10:03,850
When you're older, you'll understand that every woman should keep at least some secrets.

174
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:09,160
See, and you were worried nobody would dance with you, and look how popular you were.

175
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,840
Dad, what was taking turns on me was the class rejects.

176
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,700
You and Lexa actually looked pretty good together.

177
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:18,850
I just don't know why you then picked the big girl.

178
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:21,910
And you, Saša, why didn't you dance?

179
00:10:22,050 --> 00:10:24,590
Nobody came for me, Mr. Pacovský.

180
00:10:24,850 --> 00:10:26,970
And what about that boy who was almost hugging you?

181
00:10:26,970 --> 00:10:27,870
Where did you two go?

182
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:30,850
That was Voráček.

183
00:10:31,850 --> 00:10:38,250
Those chains first got into his eyes, so he sat on me, then grabbed my hair with both hands and we had to go to the bathroom.

184
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:38,820
Ah.

185
00:10:39,650 --> 00:10:40,800
Iva, I'm not going back there.

186
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:45,550
At least you danced with Beneš, but I spent half the lesson with my head in the sink.

187
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,580
Beneš is an idiot.

188
00:10:46,580 --> 00:10:49,350
The whole time he kept asking me if Kropáčková is seeing anyone.

189
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:53,050
Chin up.

190
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:55,750
You wanted to talk to me, Iva?

191
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:59,250
Yeah, but in private.

192
00:11:05,670 --> 00:11:06,110
Dad.

193
00:11:07,050 --> 00:11:10,150
Yeah, yeah, sure, sure.

194
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,120
So.

195
00:11:22,550 --> 00:11:26,250
About tonight, I wanted to tell you it was pretty disgusting.

196
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,200
I know, the gloves, right?

197
00:11:28,220 --> 00:11:30,500
My hands got all sweaty and they won't come off.

198
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,100
I wanted to cut them with a razor blade, but mom must have stopped shaving her legs.

199
00:11:35,350 --> 00:11:36,260
Don't change the subject.

200
00:11:36,650 --> 00:11:38,350
You know very well what I'm talking about.

201
00:11:39,050 --> 00:11:40,450
The other disgusting thing.

202
00:11:42,650 --> 00:11:43,650
You noticed that?

203
00:11:44,150 --> 00:11:46,750
I'd only not notice if I were in a coma.

204
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:47,720
Thanks.

205
00:11:48,950 --> 00:11:50,080
I'm not complimenting you.

206
00:11:50,350 --> 00:11:52,250
I'm asking you to stop it.

207
00:11:52,460 --> 00:11:53,480
Stop what?

208
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,380
Just don't do it.

209
00:11:54,740 --> 00:11:55,840
It happens on its own.

210
00:11:56,040 --> 00:11:57,360
Then make it not happen on my leg.

211
00:11:58,820 --> 00:11:59,260
Dad!

212
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:00,700
I'm, I'm not listening.

213
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:02,420
Just checking if the door closes.

214
00:12:04,450 --> 00:12:07,420
It's because we were rubbing against each other during the dance.

215
00:12:07,650 --> 00:12:08,980
Everyone was rubbing against each other.

216
00:12:08,980 --> 00:12:10,240
Well that's exactly the problem.

217
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:14,050
When there's rubbing, it just gets bigger.

218
00:12:14,150 --> 00:12:15,920
Wait, you had it with someone else too?

219
00:12:16,050 --> 00:12:16,950
With all of them.

220
00:12:17,850 --> 00:12:18,750
Except Krutová.

221
00:12:19,750 --> 00:12:21,450
So it's actually a compliment for you.

222
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:26,630
A compliment is when someone compliments my hairdo, not when something pokes me in the stomach.

223
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:28,130
So I'll dance with Krutová then.

224
00:12:29,250 --> 00:12:31,250
Excuse me, I'm going to get water, I'm thirsty.

225
00:12:32,450 --> 00:12:34,450
You have a really nice dress, Iva.

226
00:12:35,670 --> 00:12:36,770
Thanks, Lexa.

227
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:39,130
Don't let us disturb you.

228
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,050
And you, Lexa, why are you just standing around?

229
00:12:42,550 --> 00:12:44,750
Yeah, that's exactly what I was just telling him.

230
00:12:46,450 --> 00:12:47,550
But he's just leaving.

231
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:54,050
So is that everything you needed to know?

232
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:56,850
Yeah, I don't need to see any more.

233
00:12:57,010 --> 00:12:58,390
Well remember it well.

234
00:12:58,390 --> 00:13:00,650
Well young man, come again sometime.

235
00:13:00,870 --> 00:13:01,890
No, dammit!

236
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:03,230
What is this slime?

237
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,130
No, it's not slime, it's the gloves.

238
00:13:05,670 --> 00:13:06,150
Yikes.

239
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:09,950
Sorry, Mr. Pacovský, mom must have stopped shaving her legs.

240
00:13:15,210 --> 00:13:15,690
Lexa?

241
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:18,820
I thought you had extras.

242
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:20,600
Then buy me a different dress!

243
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:32,750
Let me tell you, Marcelka, these dance classes for adults are a wonderful thing.

244
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:34,720
I'll leave this dress here.

245
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:37,460
Zoran doesn't need to know what we've been up to.

246
00:13:37,950 --> 00:13:40,580
And those ladies, how tastefully and decently they were dressed.

247
00:13:40,580 --> 00:13:41,840
Iva should see that.

248
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:48,150
That's probably because we ended up with the seniors during placement because of you.

249
00:13:48,420 --> 00:13:51,160
Ah, so that's why there was an ambulance outside.

250
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:56,150
And how useful it was when you fell during the jive with that old lady and ripped off her skirt.

251
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:59,950
Well, these Latin dances aren't my strong suit.

252
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:04,650
But her bra from East Germany really livened things up, didn't it?

253
00:14:05,050 --> 00:14:07,350
I'm actually quite happy with myself.

254
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:09,550
I'm just a little worried about the tango.

255
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:12,950
Just about the tango?

256
00:14:13,550 --> 00:14:14,350
Tomáš, the extended evening is approaching.

257
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:19,540
And the only thing you've somewhat managed so far is the turn.

258
00:14:19,850 --> 00:14:22,650
And that won't be enough for the parents' dance.

259
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:25,350
We need to intensify the practice.

260
00:14:54,450 --> 00:14:57,750
I'll be back in 20 minutes and I'll pretend I didn't see anything.

261
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:07,870
That's weak.

262
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,050
Don't you have it in that orange bottle?

263
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:13,550
You said that was a girly drink.

264
00:15:14,550 --> 00:15:16,350
I need to clear my head.

265
00:15:17,980 --> 00:15:18,500
Thanks.

266
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:24,950
So should I start making cocktails from it?

267
00:15:25,150 --> 00:15:27,490
Lately you've been at the bar more than at work.

268
00:15:27,650 --> 00:15:29,350
Bro is probably hooking up with mambo.

269
00:15:30,050 --> 00:15:32,850
They're off somewhere together at night and during the day they throw me out of the store.

270
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:36,050
Today I caught them doing some weird rituals.

271
00:15:38,950 --> 00:15:43,050
Mom, I've got a big problem at dance class.

272
00:15:44,950 --> 00:15:47,370
Lexa, dance class will change a lot of things in your life.

273
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:50,050
Everyone ignored me at dance class too.

274
00:15:50,450 --> 00:15:52,650
Finish telling him, please, I need to go to the bathroom.

275
00:15:54,550 --> 00:15:55,750
You can go by yourself.

276
00:15:56,550 --> 00:15:58,050
The junkyard is always open.

277
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:00,350
But you'd have to be a real tough guy for that.

278
00:16:00,650 --> 00:16:01,430
Exactly.

279
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,950
Iva says I'm too hard.

280
00:16:04,650 --> 00:16:05,710
So what's the problem?

281
00:16:06,050 --> 00:16:06,930
Down there.

282
00:16:06,930 --> 00:16:07,410
Hard.

283
00:16:07,950 --> 00:16:08,950
If you know what I mean.

284
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:09,770
Oh, I see.

285
00:16:09,770 --> 00:16:12,110
Welcome to manhood, Lexa.

286
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:15,020
A world of unprecedented possibilities is opening up for you.

287
00:16:15,050 --> 00:16:17,750
I know a guy who opens beers with his.

288
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:20,470
Yeah, but I'd rather get rid of it.

289
00:16:20,750 --> 00:16:23,230
Iva is mad at me, she's threatening to kick my teeth out.

290
00:16:23,230 --> 00:16:23,910
She does kickboxing.

291
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:27,750
You don't think you're the first guy in the world with this problem?

292
00:16:28,450 --> 00:16:31,350
And why do you think the president has a podium in front of him during speeches?

293
00:16:32,650 --> 00:16:34,250
That never occurred to me.

294
00:16:34,650 --> 00:16:37,450
Yeah but a podium won't help me, I need to get rid of it.

295
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:39,550
Have you tried sex?

296
00:16:40,250 --> 00:16:41,750
Got anything more realistic?

297
00:16:41,750 --> 00:16:43,550
Then the only option is the Eskimo.

298
00:16:44,650 --> 00:16:45,550
What's the Eskimo?

299
00:16:46,050 --> 00:16:46,890
Well, my boy.

300
00:16:47,650 --> 00:16:48,950
You're going to have to grit your teeth.

301
00:16:49,430 --> 00:16:49,890
Simona!

302
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:51,250
Got any ice?

303
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:53,050
Downstairs under the bar!

304
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,010
It's happening to you again.

305
00:16:56,650 --> 00:17:00,550
Mom was full of it.

306
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:06,460
Still nobody's coming for me.

307
00:17:06,500 --> 00:17:08,540
Not even Voráček, now that he can see again.

308
00:17:09,650 --> 00:17:10,650
This sucks.

309
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:14,450
Dance class is almost over, Beneš is still acting like an idiot.

310
00:17:15,850 --> 00:17:18,550
At least I don't need the ice anymore.

311
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:21,440
Iva!

312
00:17:22,050 --> 00:17:22,750
Package!

313
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:23,280
Next!

314
00:17:31,770 --> 00:17:32,230
What?

315
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:33,190
What what?

316
00:17:33,550 --> 00:17:34,130
About that?

317
00:17:35,010 --> 00:17:35,610
Oh that!

318
00:17:37,100 --> 00:17:37,780
Nothing, I think?

319
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:38,780
Great!

320
00:17:39,850 --> 00:17:42,020
Well, I'm gonna go play somewhere.

321
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:49,720
This sucks.

322
00:17:50,050 --> 00:17:51,250
Why did you pick me?

323
00:17:51,650 --> 00:17:53,180
Why not Kropáčková for example?

324
00:17:53,550 --> 00:17:55,750
He'd like to, but I don't want to.

325
00:17:56,550 --> 00:17:57,950
Kropáčková is such a tramp.

326
00:17:58,050 --> 00:18:00,200
She dresses like a slut and everyone eats it up.

327
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,580
But that's over now.

328
00:18:02,350 --> 00:18:03,500
What are you going to do?

329
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:06,350
Well some things are important and some less so.

330
00:18:07,650 --> 00:18:10,250
This, for example, was originally the gas bill payment.

331
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:35,050
Marcelka, I want to thank you so much.

332
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:37,870
I feel like I'm really going to tear it up at the extended evening.

333
00:18:37,870 --> 00:18:39,110
I'm in perfect shape.

334
00:18:40,950 --> 00:18:43,450
Save my spot and I'll pop out for a moment.

335
00:18:45,950 --> 00:18:46,940
He's completely out of it.

336
00:18:47,250 --> 00:18:48,640
He confuses the cha-cha with the polka.

337
00:18:49,350 --> 00:18:51,540
And during the waltz he hangs laundry.

338
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:52,480
Are you surprised?

339
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:54,600
Do you know what Harapes calls him?

340
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:58,250
I just dread him inviting me to the extended evening.

341
00:18:58,480 --> 00:19:02,980
This is pretty good.

342
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:03,540
What is it?

343
00:19:04,140 --> 00:19:05,000
Sunshine cocktail.

344
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:09,150
A female dancer could just beat the man to a pulp afterwards.

345
00:19:10,950 --> 00:19:12,590
Marcelka, I wanted to ask.

346
00:19:12,590 --> 00:19:13,850
Can Zoran dance too?

347
00:19:14,010 --> 00:19:15,130
Oh, no, not at all.

348
00:19:15,410 --> 00:19:17,650
Zoran only knows the Croatian victory dance.

349
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:22,150
But they banned him from shooting an automatic rifle into the ceiling at the bar, so we don't go out anymore.

350
00:19:25,750 --> 00:19:27,150
I'd like to officially invite you to Iva's extended evening.

351
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:31,620
We're really going to tear it up.

352
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,200
One more, Simona.

353
00:19:38,850 --> 00:19:40,350
Iva, hurry up, we'll be late.

354
00:19:51,650 --> 00:19:52,750
Dad's going to kill you.

355
00:19:52,780 --> 00:19:54,320
Better dead than ugly, right?

356
00:19:56,150 --> 00:19:57,050
Sorry, Saša.

357
00:19:57,450 --> 00:19:59,250
Kropáčková is going to be furious.

358
00:20:03,850 --> 00:20:04,950
There's no cooling this down.

359
00:20:07,620 --> 00:20:08,440
Hi, Lexa.

360
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:10,040
Hi, Saša.

361
00:20:10,250 --> 00:20:10,960
Hi, dad.

362
00:20:12,050 --> 00:20:14,950
You've dolled yourself up.

363
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:19,020
You can't go in that.

364
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:20,180
Dad, calm down.

365
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:22,650
It's a perfectly normal dress.

366
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,360
A normal dress?

367
00:20:25,850 --> 00:20:28,730
Just so you know, I'm not going to any extended evening with you.

368
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:37,050
I wanted to have a normal dance with my daughter, a lady, not show up with someone where you can practically see everything.

369
00:20:39,450 --> 00:20:41,950
You look like a regular hooker.

370
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:43,850
So what's the hold-up?

371
00:20:47,450 --> 00:20:48,330
Anything else?

372
00:20:48,650 --> 00:20:49,850
No, we're good.

373
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:52,050
Alright, let's go.

374
00:20:53,350 --> 00:20:54,450
Nice dress.

375
00:20:55,150 --> 00:20:55,670
Thanks.

376
00:20:59,750 --> 00:21:12,750
What are you doing here?

377
00:21:13,050 --> 00:21:14,550
You should've been dancing for half an hour, right?

378
00:21:14,850 --> 00:21:17,190
Mom, I'm not going back there, nobody asks me to dance.

379
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:20,950
You've always been a difficult child, haven't you?

380
00:21:21,350 --> 00:21:22,050
Here, drink this.

381
00:21:23,950 --> 00:21:26,050
Will this make boys dance with me?

382
00:21:26,550 --> 00:21:28,650
No, but you won't care anymore.

383
00:21:30,450 --> 00:21:31,830
Now what are you doing here?

384
00:21:32,050 --> 00:21:34,890
Mom, Krutová tried to drag me to the basement during the polka.

385
00:21:34,890 --> 00:21:36,070
She almost dislocated my shoulder.

386
00:21:36,450 --> 00:21:37,650
And you didn't go for it?

387
00:21:38,050 --> 00:21:38,550
No, I escaped during the mazurka.

388
00:21:40,390 --> 00:21:41,610
Then you're an idiot.

389
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:44,450
We get a five-grand bonus for the basement.

390
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:48,480
I just realized you're basically my pimp.

391
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:52,450
But a loving and caring pimp, you could've done much worse.

392
00:21:53,050 --> 00:21:54,850
I should've run away to the junkyard.

393
00:21:57,170 --> 00:21:57,650
Scram.

394
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:15,000
I don't know how it happened, must've been the turn.

395
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:19,540
If you're going to keep falling, at least stop trying to grab your partner's clothes.

396
00:22:19,740 --> 00:22:23,060
I'm sorry, Marcelka, it was a reflex, anyone would've done it.

397
00:22:23,280 --> 00:22:24,260
Harapes's move.

398
00:22:24,850 --> 00:22:26,850
And call me a taxi.

399
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:31,090
If someone photographed us and sends that photo to Zoran, you're dead.

400
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:32,450
And I'm divorced.

401
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:34,410
Thanks.

402
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:36,300
Clorex.

403
00:22:36,300 --> 00:22:39,220
I save that for special occasions.

404
00:22:39,220 --> 00:22:40,040
One more.

405
00:22:40,280 --> 00:22:41,140
Am I paying for this?

406
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,920
That's what you wanted.

407
00:22:44,420 --> 00:22:47,440
Marcelka, could you please give me back my jacket?

408
00:22:47,540 --> 00:22:49,460
The parents' dance is coming up.

409
00:22:49,930 --> 00:22:52,010
So I'm supposed to sit here naked?

410
00:22:52,150 --> 00:22:54,270
Well, Simona will lend you something.

411
00:22:54,850 --> 00:22:55,650
You know what.

412
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:57,220
All I have is tablecloths.

413
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:02,520
Zero!

414
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,650
You know what, it's working, Voráček took me to the park.

415
00:23:08,650 --> 00:23:10,550
Girl, you're a shark.

416
00:23:10,880 --> 00:23:12,100
Silent and deadly.

417
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,960
But I think it's wearing off.

418
00:23:14,980 --> 00:23:16,380
Sometimes he stops seeing me.

419
00:23:16,460 --> 00:23:18,080
Saša, don't overdo it too much.

420
00:23:18,650 --> 00:23:20,680
Oh no, mom, we're just holding hands.

421
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:21,560
I mean with the booze.

422
00:23:23,950 --> 00:23:24,650
You drank the entire gas payment.

423
00:23:40,350 --> 00:23:42,530
Sorry, I just can't handle this Jack.

424
00:23:42,670 --> 00:23:43,530
Just shut up now, please.

425
00:23:43,910 --> 00:23:45,470
Ivuška, fancy something blue?

426
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:47,350
I feel like murdering someone.

427
00:23:47,350 --> 00:23:51,830
My darling, I called the store about cleaning up during the extended evening.

428
00:23:52,150 --> 00:23:53,170
I'm not wearing anything at all.

429
00:23:53,170 --> 00:23:55,390
I'm perfectly fine with this tablecloth.

430
00:23:55,910 --> 00:23:57,170
Where's that taxi?

431
00:24:03,150 --> 00:24:03,950
A miracle.

432
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:06,490
Drop dead, Lexa.

433
00:24:06,650 --> 00:24:09,050
This sucks.

434
00:24:09,950 --> 00:24:11,900
You're the worst dancer in the world.

435
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:13,440
Yeah dad, you ruined everything.

436
00:24:13,740 --> 00:24:15,040
The dress would've worked on them.

437
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,660
He didn't even notice Kropáčková.

438
00:24:17,260 --> 00:24:19,340
I could feel him being interested in me.

439
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,120
And you don't mind that at all?

440
00:24:21,260 --> 00:24:22,480
Lexa, think about Krutová, okay?

441
00:24:27,450 --> 00:24:29,080
I'm not pouring you another shot.

442
00:24:29,350 --> 00:24:30,300
I don't care.

443
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:31,420
See, it works?

444
00:24:31,420 --> 00:24:36,700
Voráček spent half an hour trying to rip my dress off, but he couldn't even undo a sleeve.

445
00:24:36,700 --> 00:24:38,220
Then he fell asleep from exhaustion.

446
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:42,680
Yeah, they survived thirty years underground, they can survive anything.

447
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,380
Sorry, Saša.

448
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:45,720
I don't care.

449
00:24:46,560 --> 00:24:47,760
See, I told you.

450
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:51,040
With a proper dress, you wouldn't have had a problem with me during the jive.

451
00:24:51,250 --> 00:24:53,850
What's wrong with wanting people to notice me?

452
00:24:54,110 --> 00:24:55,590
Well then you can be happy.

453
00:24:55,670 --> 00:24:57,210
They won't forget our jive anytime soon.

454
00:24:57,250 --> 00:24:58,790
And our tango.

455
00:25:02,050 --> 00:25:05,250
Wow, I didn't know dance class was this much fun.

456
00:25:06,450 --> 00:25:10,750
Mommy, I brought you that bag that's been lying around in the storage room.

457
00:25:11,820 --> 00:25:12,300
Thank you.

458
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:17,450
You go get dressed and hurry back so you can at least make the last dance.

459
00:25:18,150 --> 00:25:19,210
I'm not going anywhere.

460
00:25:19,550 --> 00:25:24,350
No, look, if you won't go to the music, the music will come to you.

461
00:25:30,050 --> 00:25:31,250
Just not the tango.

462
00:26:34,010 --> 00:26:34,670
Good afternoon.

463
00:26:35,090 --> 00:26:35,650
Is zero here?

464
00:26:39,150 --> 00:26:39,550
In the back.
